               <p>I was coming down Fleet-street, and I see three young men together, and 
               <persName id="t17940430-113-person1144">
                  Thomas
                   Davis
               <interp inst="t17940430-113-person1144" type="surname" value="Davis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-113-person1144" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-113-person1144" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was the first, and I see him make a motion to this gentleman's pocket, and picked it of his handkerchief, and I stepped up to the gentleman, and told him, and the gentleman turned round and catched him in his hand.</p>
               <p>- sworn.</p>
               <p>I am an officer, this handkerchief was given me by Mr. Dudge.</p>
               <p>Dudge. This is my handkerchief.</p>

               <p>Hart. This is the handkerchief I saw taken out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I belong to an India man, I have been had with an ague and fever a long time, and am really distressed.</p>
